A week ago the lord revealed to me that this ring was an idol. The dream was so vivid and clear. I should of did it right away but it was hard being that I’m still until this day healing from so much when it comes to this company.
Yesterday I went to church and when I tell you I felt the presence of God hover over me😫 my entire body got weak and he said you have given many advice on going back to a path they don’t belong to. He said I know you are hurt and in pain but some people are not ready to hear that just yet. He said I need you to let that part of your life go and he also confirmed my dream letting me know to remove that idol from my home and close that chapter because he has bigger and better for me and he is proud of me for trusting him.
I can’t tell you how long I cried in my car when he confirmed this to me. That’s all I needed. Was for God himself to tell me, keep looking forward. Don’t look back.
Today I let go of a ring that reflected me making almost a million dollars with this company.. but again money isn’t everything to me. My soul is worth more than money. 
Thank you Jesus for being so real and confirming that path is not of you and your detach myself from everything attached to that old life. 
•

I just had to share this because so many close to me know there was so many times I said “I’m ok” and I wasn’t really okay.
There was times I showed up smiling, and laughing when inside I felt broken and shattered.
I just want you to know it’s ok to not be ok sometimes. It’s ok to admit it and acknowledge those feelings.
The word in church on Monday night was releasing any negative emotions, and not holding it in.
People make you think you’re weak if you cry when in reality it shows you are strong. It shows you are human. It shows you have a heart. He said cry it out because holding it in is very dangerous for your health.
That night so many of us ending crying for an hour during deliverance service and let me tell you that I walked out a brand new woman. Please don’t hold it in sis… let it out and release it to God.
If this was for you type “amen”

After replying to hundreds of DM’s one of the main questions I’ve received is how do I keep my faith in God? How did I build a strong relationship? How do you hear him speak ?
The answer to it all is fasting. I started fasting a year and a half ago and that is what has changed my life. I don’t speak of when I fast because the Bible tells us not to. My fasts are private and that’s what makes it more powerful. In Matthew chap 6 vs 16 it says: When you fast, do not look somber as the hypocrites do for they disfigure their faces to show others they are fasting. 
Verse 17- But when you fast put oil on your head and wash your face 
Verse 18- so that it will not be obvious to others that you are fasting, but only to your father who is unseen and your father who sees what is done in secret will reward you.
•
I had to quote this scripture because I remember when I would publicly announce that I am fasting and the lord revealed to me to fast in private. When you don’t announce it, your enemies don’t know what to attack. You are doing it in private and in silence where it’s just you and God.
The only time you should announce it is when you are hosting a corporate fast, meaning you are leading a group fast. I do this often and will have one soon, but when it’s on my own no one will never know because that’s between me and GOD.
•
I say all of that to say, fast for Jesus. This will help build your spiritual life, but do not announce it. 
Too often, the focus of fasting is on the lack of food. Instead, the purpose of fasting should be to take your eyes off the things of this world to focus completely on God. Fasting is a way to demonstrate to God, and to ourselves, that we are serious about our relationship with Him. Fasting helps us gain a new perspective and a renewed reliance upon God.
•
By taking our eyes off the things of this world, we can more successfully turn our attention to Christ. Fasting is not a way to get God to do what we want. Fasting changes us, not God. Fasting is not a way to appear more spiritual than others. Fasting is to be done in a spirit of humility and a joyful attitude
•
Do your fast whether it be for 3 days, 7 days, or 21 days but do it ASAP.
When you replay the audio of you singing in the car and you hear how you actually sound 🤣🤣🤣

Let’s talk about home schooling 👇🏼
•
There are two ways to get your kid into home school. You can take the easy route and discharge them from their zoned school and register them with a school online. The school online would need to provide the curriculum and they need to the state wide test yearly. 
•
The way I have my kids home schooled is with a letter of intent form through the board of education. This letter is basically saying you are going to be responsible for what you’re child is learning at their grade level. 
The reason I have my kids home schooled this way is because they all needed more one on one support or a smaller group setting and being in a class with a bunch of children online or In person just doesn’t work for them.
They was having trouble learning, especially my son considering that he had severe adhd and they continued to neglect the services he needed to be able to succeed. They kept failing my children and making them repeat the grade.
•
Once I found it with the letter of intent form you can register them at their correct grade and that they will be able to get more one on one help with me plus they don’t need a state wide test to pass I know this was best for them.
•
My son was in the “6th grade” when I registered him and they told me I can register him as an 8th grader. I was able to get him in the correct grade. You have the right to say what grade they are in. If I would of kept my kids in school they wouldn’t be in the correct grade level, but i took charge and got them back in their right grade. My son will be graduating this year 😍 and my daughters are doing amazing!
•
One Of the systems I use online which isn’t a school it’s an educational system is www.timeforlearning.com
It allows them to work at their own pace on the grade level they are in and builds a portfolio for the annual teacher to review yearly.
•
I run multiple businesses from home and still make time to make sure my babies are learning and progressing. I’ll post a photo in my stories on what a passing letter looks like from the annual certified teacher

Let’s talk AIRBNB 🗣
This is how the process works & what will learn more in detail in my course 
•
We find short term rentals that’s in beautiful community and email them to ask if they accept corporate leasing.
•
If they say YES we then ask if it’s possible to move in on the 15th of the month. The reason we do this is so we can pay a PRO RATED rent charge but we still pay the FULL security amount.
•
There is a website we use (it’s in my course) to make sure the nightly rate I want to charge fits the zip code budget, I check the occupancy rate as well as the monthly revenue rate. If everything looks good, I PROCEED.
•
I always set a budget for each property on how much it will be for expenses, furniture, etc. we have the plug for fancy yet affordable furniture (it’s in the course) and once I make sure it’s an investment that’s in my budget I continue to proceed with the process.
•
I also check how much I would make if I booked 25 nights a month to make sure the profit makes sense 💯
The reason I say 25 nights is because let’s be realistic you need days in between for the cleaners to come fix up the place. 
If the profit monthly & yearly makes sense I move forward with my business.
•
Two properties with the same profit can have you well over 6 figures a year. It’s a nice business module and with proper structure in placement you can be successful 
•
There are MANY OF WAYS to do the Airbnb business and this is one of the ways it works and NO ONE and I mean absolutely NO ONE can tell me it doesn’t work because I currently do it and make well over 6 figures with just one property but that’s because my property is near Disney world and is in a tourist area so the occupancy is HIGH as well as the revenue in this specific area. 
Keep in mind we can both have a 3 bedroom 2 bathroom which is what I have but my area can be in a more attractive area and make more money then yours.
This is why it’s important to follow the instructions in my course and not rush the process.

Here are some things you need to know for Shopify capital 

You need to have a Shopify store that has been active for at least six months and has generated a minimum of $10,000 in revenue. I have seen people get offers before achieving this goal, but this is usually the minimum requirement. 

To increase your chances of getting approved for shopify capital, it’s important to have a solid business plan, a clear understanding of your financials, and a track record of consistent sales. You should also make sure that your story is optimized for conversions, and that you’re actively promoting your business through social media. 

Overall, shopify can be a great way to obtain funding for your business as long as you meet the eligibility requirements and have a clear plan for how you will use the funds to grow your store.

This post reminds me when my husband and I decided to take a leap of faith, move out of the Bronx and start a new life in Florida with our kids. I had a new baby 2 months before this photo, and we had faith that God will go with us wherever we go. 

When I look at the woman in this photo, I admire her because she was brave, resilient and fearless. We worked so hard, saved up money and got a new house in Florida. 

The transition wasn’t easy, I remember saying the first year how much I wanted to back to New York. But the Lord spoke to me in prophecy and told me “This is where I have called you, this is where you will serve me. It is me who brought you here, he said I will be using you to speak in prophecy, lay hands on healing and to travel around the world to lay hands on healing”. 

I left church feeling overwhelmed because I had to accept that this is where the Lord called me, but also I didn’t feel I qualified to do any of those things. I said God these promise sounds wonderful but I’m not perfect. How will I be able to do these things? 

It wasn’t to long after that I realized all I had to do was surrender. When I surrendered fully it was my yes that allowed my kids and husband to follow. Most times it’s the man who leads but in my case, I had to be obedient and submit myself to the Lord and my husband was amazed at how God was moving in my life and submitted as well. Now he is the one who leads this family, gathers us in prayer, reads the Bible with us, we go to church together and live a life for Christ. 

Today, I have a powerful ministry that God has his hands on. I have been used and still continue to be used in the prophetic, I have delivered people and he has also used me for hands on healing. 

God is NOT a God that lies. Every promise he has made me he always kept, I give him all honor and glory for all he has done through me and continues to do. 

I share all of this to say you never know where your YES can take you! Take that leap of faith. Start over new! God is with you wherever you go. Surrender to the Lord and let him use you. You may have flaws, but you are still USABLE. 

Sincerely, 
~ A womanwhoprays
